<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-424-881  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 424 881.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 10 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Seagate claims world's fastest disk drives. (Seagate TechnologyInc.'s ST1480 and ST1400 hard disk drives) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Seagate Technology Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    SGAT.andO;Product:   Seagate Technology ST1480 (Hard disk drive) (product introduction)Seagate Technology ST1400 (Hard disk drive) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionHard DiskDisk Drives.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SEAGATE CLAIMS WORLD'S FASTEST DISK DRIVES SCOTTS VALLEY, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A.,andO;1990 JUL 6 (NB) -- Seagate Technologies says it has created 3.5-inch diskdrives with the world's fastest data access speed of 6.8 milliseconds.andP;  TheST1480 and ST1400 hard disk drives utilize Seagate's Zone Bit Recordingtechnology.andP;  Both products have a spindle rotation speed of 4400 RPM(revolutions per minute).andM;Coupled with a 14-millisecond average seek time for both read and writecommands, the data transfer rates to and from the 426 and 331-megabyte disksare as high as 25 megabits per second, according to the company.andM;Seagate says a number of evaluation units have been placed at various OEM(original equipment manufacturer) client sites, and that the drives will becommercially available during the fourth quarter of this year.andM;(Wendy Woods/19900705/Press Contact: Julie Still, Seagate, 408-439-2276)</TEXT></DOC>